{"questionId":"27855","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Giles charges a customer per hour to hire his boat. It is known that</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>980</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is the cost per hour, in Norwegian krone (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>NOK</mtext></math>), that the customer is charged and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;is the time, in hours, spent on the boat.</p>\n<p>The cost per hour has a local minimum when the boat is hired for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> hours.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>980</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept equivalent information presented in a labelled sketch.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;hours&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A0</strong> </em>for an answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>280</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27855","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.13a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of h.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}